### ERROR TIPS

#### Errors when placing pipes
- Ensure that the target location for placing a pipe is free from any existing objects. If an object is present, remove it before attempting to place the pipe.
- Double-check the target location coordinates to ensure they are not already occupied by another entity.

#### Connection Errors
- Ensure that all components of the electricity generator, such as the boiler and steam engine, are properly connected to each other and to the power network.
- Verify that all necessary input liquids are supplied to the boiler and steam engine to avoid warnings related to 'no input liquid' and 'no fluid present in connections'.
